Rachel Simpson was diagnosed with a mutation of the GATA2 gene last year . 
  She has a one-in-a-million genetic condition which doctors say will eventually give her cancer if untreated . 
  The rest of her family are now waiting on tests which could reveal which of them also have the faulty gene . 
  The disorder is important in the production of blood cells . 
  Miss Simpson's blood count might be low, making her vulnerable to infection . 
 